pull_request.title: Improve Installation and contributing instructions
pull_request.body:
Instead of having people contact us, let's power it with pull requests.

Typical open source contribution flow from what I've seen:

1. Person forks our repo
2. They make commits to implement feature/bug fix/etc. on their fork, where they have full push access and admin privileges
3. When ready, they create a pull request to merge their change(s) into our repo
4. We review the PR and approve or request some things to be changed. We can also setup Travis CI and configure it such that PRs can't be merged if they fail the CI build.
5. If one of us approves + Travis CI passes, we merge their changes into our master.

This allows anyone to start contributing right away and doesn't force us to give everyone push access :) 

Also, regarding installation instructions, we can have contributors set up their own private keys and test with their own GCP account, so they don't interfere with our testing (and eventually prod?) environments. Need more instructions for this in readme, but I placed some basics in for now.
